details: Think pedagogically to design interactive lessons, articles, and quizzes that translate complex data science concepts into accessible components.
Work with curriculum developers to establish learning standards and craft a compelling learner experience.
Collaborate with physicians and investigators in the Glickman Urological and Kidney Institute and other research departments.
Lead the design of clinical research studies, including performing sample size estimation and authoring statistical analysis plans.
Carry out analyses, develop publication-ready graphics, and interpret results using R and SAS.
Assist with writing and editing of clinical study protocols, manuscripts for peer reviewed journal submission, and grant proposals.
Supported ongoing economics/econometrics research projects in the Center for Indian Country Development.
Conducted exploratory data analysis, statistical modeling, and regression on large federal survey data.
Prepared reports using R Markdown and LaTeX that effectively communicate results of analyses to a variety of stakeholders.
Worked with a Native American CDFI to assess the efficacy of financial programs intended to build wealth in Indian Country.

Led weekly lab sessions, monitored online discussion forums, and performed grading for PUBH 6414 Biostatistical Literacy (Fall 2019, Spring 2020) and PUBH 3415/7415 Introduction to Clinical Trials (Summer 2019).
Assisted with ongoing surveillance projects in the Healthcare Associated Infections/Antibiotic Resistance Unit.
Collected, managed, and performed quality-control checks of data on reported cases of antibiotic-resistant bacteria using Microsoft Access.
Conducted reviews of electronic medical records using Epic.
Worked with a team of physicians and biostatisticians to investigate the relationship between the microbiome and pathogenesis of ventilator-associated pneumonia.
Used PCA and other non-parametric methods to analyze data from gastric and tracheal microbiomes.
Successfully used dplyr, ggplot2, phyloseq, and other packages in R to carry out data cleaning and analysis.
Negotiated clinical study contracts and budgets for 100+ research sites at any given time.
Worked collaboratively with regulatory and study management teams to meet study startup timelines.
Met with industry sponsors to establish contract and budget parameters and provide updates on contract and budget negotiations.

Assisted clinicians in the operating room with biopsy tissue collection and preparation for intraoperative diagnosis.
Communicated with physicians and hospital staff and managed testing results using Epic and Epic Beaker lab systems.
